com.remotemonster.sdk

Class Config

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.remotemonster.sdk.Config

  • public class Config
extends java.lang.Object
    Config is a way for app users to choose their preferred environment In addition to the environment, developers can customize their app The quality of the channel and the information for the connection are initially set and separated from the general remocon context information. In other words, it is to set the situation or environment that you want at the beginning of communication. This is a user, app, remon.sdk, remon.restHost It may be changed in order, and therefore it must be managed by the client continuously for each communication channel. When the channel dies, this config is released and only the defaults or defaults set by the user / service are set. It is configured in json mode.

    Author:
    Created by calmglow on 16. 8. 22., Reviser by lucas on 18. 1. 1
